records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The State moves to delete the enhancer on count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1 of deliver schedule IV drugs.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, deliver prescription drug.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of four and one half (4.5) years.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence presently being served.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Programs.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or work search;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
Minutes.
